# p99-meter — Project Overview

This is an **Electron overlay app** for EverQuest Project 1999. It parses combat logs in real-time and displays a floating damage meter overlay on top of the EQ game window.

## Codebase Location

The source code is at `Z:\Everquest P99\p99-meter\src\`.

**CRITICAL**: Do NOT confuse this with `Z:\Everquest P99\p99-armory\` which is a separate Next.js web app. The damage meter is p99-meter, NOT p99-armory. Always verify you are editing files inside `p99-meter/src/`.

## Architecture

- **Electron main process**: `src/index.ts` — window management, IPC handlers, overlay controller, log watcher, layout persistence
- **Preload bridge**: `src/preload.ts` — exposes `window.electronAPI` to renderer
- **React renderer**: `src/App.tsx` → `src/DamageMeter.tsx` — UI components
- **Combat tracking**: `src/useCombatTracker.ts` — fight state machine, entity stats
- **Log parsing**: `src/logParser.ts` — regex-based EQ log line parsing
- **Spell correlation**: `src/spellCorrelator.ts` — attributes spell damage to casters
- **Class detection**: `src/eqClasses.ts` — spell/skill to class mapping
- **NPC detection**: `src/constants.ts` — `isLikelyNPC()`, timing constants
- **Pet data**: `src/petData.ts` — pet names and summon spells
- **Spell database**: `src/spellDatabase.ts` — loads spells_us.txt
- **Class icons**: `src/classIcons.tsx` — SVG class icons

## Build & Run

- Dev: `npm start` (webpack-dev-server with HMR)
- Package: `npm run package` (outputs to `out/p99-meter-win32-x64/`)
- Type check: `npx tsc --noEmit --skipLibCheck`
- Tests: `npx vitest run`

**After source changes, the app must be rebuilt** — the packaged exe does NOT auto-update.
